Hello,

Updating a single host is easy. Rotating credentials on hundreds isn't. Unless you override group settings and use identities. In this email, you'll see how to bulk *update hundreds of hosts* in Termius.

📂 *Group settings* are applied to all hosts put inside. They inherit agent forwarding, startup snippet, jump host, proxy, etc. For complex cases, use subgroups to cascade and override parameters. You can still tweak settings for individual hosts.

🪪 *Identities* are the key for easy secrets rotation. Set a username, password, or key, and link it to your hosts and groups. When it's time to rotate, update it in the identity once, and all hosts are updated.

